property.name: text
property.value:
This demo is based on the ePlus80-actuator example provided by the Building Controls Virtual Test Bed (BCVTB). To run this demo, EnergyPlus V8.0.0 and the Building Controls Virtual Testbed are required. To generate the HTML page: File -> Export -> Export to Web.
Before launching Ptolemy, please add the following to your Eclipse run configuration. Under Run -> Run Configurations... select your Ptolemy run configuration (e.g. Vergil) Select the "Environment" tab. Select "New..." and add these two variables: Variable name: BCVTB_HOME Value: The root directory of your BCVTB installation, e.g. C:\bcvtb
Variable name: PATH Value: The root directory of your EnergyPlus installation, the EnergyPlus WeatherData directory, and the directory where java.exe is installed, e.g. C:\EnergyPlusV8-0-0;C:\EnergyPlusV8-0-0\WeatherData;C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre7\bin
Note that updating your system PATH variable is not sufficient for some reason. Maybe since the Simulator actor invokes another java process, that process doesn't have access to the system environment variables?
For more information: EnergyPlus: http://apps1.eere.energy.gov/buildings/energyplus/ BCVTB: http://simulationresearch.lbl.gov/bcvtb/
